<recipe>
	<title>North African chicken</title>
	<description>Chicken thighs cooked in a spicy chermoula paste, with cucumber, feta and cous cous</description>
	<date>20 June 2014</date>
	<source>http://www.taste.com.au/recipes/20827/north+african+chicken</source>
	<image>http://www.taste.com.au/images/recipes/sfi/2008/10/20827_l.jpg</image>
	<preparation>0:45</preparation>
	<cooking>0:15</cooking>
	<difficulty>easy</difficulty>
	<serves>4</serves>
	<author>Claire Brookman</author>
	<genre type="region">Africa</genre>
	<genre type="ingredient">meat/chicken</genre>
	<ingredients>
		<item id="1">Lebanese cucumber(s)</item>
		<item id="2">red onion(s)</item>
		<item id="3">fresh mint leaf/leaves</item>
		<item id="4">feta cheese</item>
		<item id="5">lemon(s)</item>
		<item id="6">olive oil</item>
		<item id="7">cous cous</item>
		<item id="8">tomato(es)</item>
		<item id="9">red capsicum pepper(s)</item>
		<item id="10">small brown onion(s)</item>
		<item id="11">balsamic vinegar</item>
		<item id="12">chicken thigh fillet(s)</item>
		<item id="13">garlic</item>
		<item id="14">fresh coriander leaf/leaves</item>
		<item id="15">fresh parsley leaf/leaves</item>
		<item id="16">ground cumin</item>
		<item id="17">mild paprika</item>
		<item id="18">ground cinnamon</item>
		<item id="19">cayenne pepper</item>
		<item id="20">salt</item>
	</ingredients>
	<dish>
		<name>Chermoula chicken</name>
		<ingredient id="12.1">
			<quantity>700</quantity>
			<unit>g</unit>
			<prep>trimmed and roughly diced</prep>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="13.1">
			<quantity>2</quantity>
			<unit>clove(s)</unit>
			<prep>chopped</prep>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="10.1">
			<quantity>1</quantity>
			<prep>thinly sliced</prep>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="14.1">
			<quantity>0.5</quantity>
			<unit>cup(s)</unit>
			<prep>roughly chopped</prep>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="15.1">
			<quantity>1</quantity>
			<unit>cup(s)</unit>
			<prep>roughly chopped</prep>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="16.1">
			<quantity>1</quantity>
			<unit>tablespoon(s)</unit>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="17.1">
			<quantity>2</quantity>
			<unit>teaspoon(s)</unit>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="18.1">
			<quantity>0.5</quantity>
			<unit>teaspoon(s)</unit>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="19.1">
			<quantity>1</quantity>
			<unit>pinch(es)</unit>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="5.2">
			<quantity>0.5</quantity>
			<prep>juiced</prep>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="6.3">
			<quantity>1</quantity>
			<unit>tablespoon(s)</unit>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="20.1"/>
		<step>Place [garlic|13.1], [onion|10.1], [coriander|14.1], [parsley|15.1], [cumin|16.1], [paprika|17.1], [cinnamon|18.1], [cayenne pepper|19.1], [lemon juice|5.2] and [olive oil|6.3] in a food processor and season with [salt|20.1]. Blend until almost smooth.</step>
		<step>Spoon the chermoula paste into a large bowl and add the [chicken thighs|12.1]. Turn the chicken until coated all over.</step>
		<step>Heat olive oil in a large frying pan and add the chicken. Fry with any remaining paste until the chicken is cooked through.</step>
		<step>Serve with cucumber salad and cous cous.</step>
	</dish>
	<dish>
		<name>Cous cous</name>
		<ingredient id="7.1">
			<quantity>1.3</quantity>
			<unit>cup(s)</unit>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="8.1">
			<quantity>2</quantity>
			<prep>chopped</prep>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="9.1">
			<quantity>0.5</quantity>
			<prep>chopped</prep>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="2.2">
			<quantity>0.5</quantity>
			<prep>chopped</prep>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="4.2">
			<quantity>40</quantity>
			<unit>g</unit>
			<prep>crumbled</prep>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="6.2">
			<quantity>1</quantity>
			<unit>tablespoon(s)</unit>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="11.1">
			<quantity>2</quantity>
			<unit>tablespoon(s)</unit>
		</ingredient>
		<step>Meanwhile, cook the [cous cous|7.1] according to its packet instructions and move to a large bowl. Add the [tomatoes|8.1], [red pepper|9.1], [onion|2.2], [feta|4.2] [olive oil|6.2] and [vinegar|11.1] and toss together.</step>
	</dish>
	<dish>
		<name>Cucumber salad</name>
		<ingredient id="1.1">
			<quantity>1</quantity>
			<prep>halved and sliced</prep>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="2.1">
			<quantity>0.5</quantity>
			<prep>thinly sliced</prep>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="3.1">
			<quantity>0.33</quantity>
			<unit>cup(s)</unit>
			<prep>roughly chopped</prep>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="4.1">
			<quantity>60</quantity>
			<unit>g</unit>
			<prep>crumbled</prep>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="5.1">
			<quantity>0.5</quantity>
			<prep>juiced</prep>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient id="6.1">
			<quantity>1</quantity>
			<unit>tablespoon(s)</unit>
		</ingredient>
		<step>Place the [cucumber|1.1], [onion|2.1], [mint|3.1], [feta|4.1], [lemon juice|5.1] and [olive oil|6.1] in a bowl and toss to combine.</step>
	</dish>
</recipe>
